# Force delta to use the actual fzf preview-pane width instead of the parent
# shell's $COLUMNS. Without this, side-by-side diffs in `glo`/`gd` previews
# render at full-terminal width and get cropped to ~60% by fzf, producing
# cramped columns and a large empty area on the right of the preview pane.
# Single-quoted so the ${FZF_PREVIEW_COLUMNS:-$COLUMNS} expansion is deferred
# to preview time, where forgit `eval`s this string inside the bash preview
# subshell (FORGIT_IN_PREVIEW=1). Host-wide `git diff`, lazygit, and gh-dash
# keep using the unmodified `delta` from core.pager — this only affects forgit
# preview rendering, and recomputes on every fzf re-render so terminal resize
